This paper discusses the emergence of language through a game-like model, which is a common topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also explores the role of noise in communication, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the study of language evolution and dynamics can fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SD).
